find_duplicates <- function(data) {
  results <- c()
  for (i in 1:nrow(data)) {
    for (j in 1:nrow(data)) {
      if (i != j && data[i, 1] == data[j, 1]) {
        results <- c(results, i)
      }
    }
  }
  unique(results)
}

# Test 3: Code to explain (using tidyverse patterns)
analyze_iris <- function() {
  iris %>%
    group_by(Species) %>%
    summarise(
      mean_length = mean(Sepal.Length),
      sd_length = sd(Sepal.Length),
      n = n()
    ) %>%
    arrange(desc(mean_length))
}

# Test 4: Simple data manipulation
process_data <- function(df, threshold = 50) {
  filtered <- df[df$value > threshold, ]
  filtered$normalized <- filtered$value / max(filtered$value)
  return(filtered)
}

#' Explain Code from Console
#'
#' Explains R code directly from the console. Can accept code as a string,
#' expression, or will use clipboard if no argument provided.
#'
#' @param code Optional code to explain. If NULL, uses clipboard.
#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to claude_query
#'
#' @return Character string with explanation
#' @export
#' @examples
#' \dontrun{
#' # Explain code from string
#' explain("lm(mpg ~ wt, data = mtcars)")
#'
#' # Copy code to clipboard, then:
#' explain()
#' }
explain <- function(code = NULL, ...) {
  # Get code from argument or clipboard
  code_text <- get_code_input(code, "explain")

  if (is.null(code_text)) {
    return(invisible(NULL))
  }

  prompt <- paste(
    "Please explain this R code clearly and concisely:",
    "",
    "- What does it do?",
    "- Key logic or algorithms used",
    "- Any potential issues or improvements",
    "",
    "Keep the explanation accessible for R programmers.",
    sep = "\n"
  )

  context <- list(
    selection = code_text,
    language = "r"
  )

  result <- claude_query(
    prompt = prompt,
    context = context,
    ...
  )

  print_response(result)
  invisible(result)
}


#' Improve Code from Console
#'
#' Gets improvement suggestions for R code from the console.
#'
#' @param code Optional code to improve. If NULL, uses clipboard.
#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to claude_query
#'
#' @return Character string with improved code
#' @export
#' @examples
#' \dontrun{
#' # Improve code from string
#' improve("for(i in 1:10) { print(i) }")
#'
#' # Copy code to clipboard, then:
#' improve()
#' }
improve <- function(code = NULL, ...) {
  code_text <- get_code_input(code, "improve")

  if (is.null(code_text)) {
    return(invisible(NULL))
  }

  prompt <- paste(
    "Please improve this R code for:",
    "- Performance and efficiency",
    "- Readability and clarity",
    "- R best practices and idioms",
    "- Error handling where appropriate",
    "",
    "Provide:",
    "1. The improved code (in a code block)",
    "2. A brief explanation of the key improvements made",
    "",
    "Keep improvements practical and focused. Don't over-engineer.",
    sep = "\n"
  )

  context <- list(
    selection = code_text,
    language = "r"
  )

  result <- claude_query(
    prompt = prompt,
    context = context,
    ...
  )

  print_response(result)
  invisible(result)
}


#' Generate Documentation from Console
#'
#' Generates roxygen2 documentation for an R function from the console.
#'
#' @param code Optional function code. If NULL, uses clipboard.
#' @param ... Additional arguments passed to claude_query
#'
#' @return Character string with roxygen2 documentation
#' @export
#' @examples
#' \dontrun{
#' # Document a function
#' document("my_func <- function(x, y) { x + y }")
#'
#' # Copy function to clipboard, then:
#' document()
#' }
document <- function(code = NULL, ...) {
  code_text <- get_code_input(code, "document")

  if (is.null(code_text)) {
    return(invisible(NULL))
  }

  prompt <- paste(
    "Generate roxygen2 documentation for this R function.",
    "",
    "Include:",
    "- #' @title (short, descriptive title)",
    "- #' @description (1-2 sentence description)",
    "- #' @param for each parameter (with type and description)",
    "- #' @return (describe what the function returns)",
    "- #' @examples (at least 2 realistic examples)",
    "- #' @export (if this should be an exported function)",
    "",
    "Format:",
    "- Start each line with #'",
    "- Use proper roxygen2 syntax",
    "- Make examples runnable when possible",
    "- Be concise but informative",
    "",
    "Return ONLY the roxygen2 comments, not the function itself.",
    sep = "\n"
  )

  context <- list(
    selection = code_text,
    language = "r"
  )

  result <- claude_query(
    prompt = prompt,
    context = context,
    ...
  )

  print_response(result)
  invisible(result)
}


#' Get Code Input from Various Sources
#'
#' Helper to get code from argument, clipboard, or prompt user.
#'
#' @param code Code argument (can be NULL, character, or expression)
#' @param action_name Name of action for messages
#'
#' @return Character string with code, or NULL if cancelled
#' @noRd
get_code_input <- function(code, action_name = "process") {
  # If code provided as argument
  if (!is.null(code)) {
    # Handle expressions
    if (is.expression(code) || is.call(code)) {
      return(deparse(code))
    }

    # Handle character
    if (is.character(code)) {
      return(paste(code, collapse = "\n"))
    }

    # Try to deparse other objects
    return(deparse(substitute(code)))
  }

  # Try clipboard
  if (requireNamespace("clipr", quietly = TRUE)) {
    tryCatch({
      clipboard_content <- clipr::read_clip()
      if (length(clipboard_content) > 0 && nchar(paste(clipboard_content, collapse = "")) > 0) {
        cli::cli_alert_info("Using code from clipboard")
        return(paste(clipboard_content, collapse = "\n"))
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      # Clipboard failed, continue to interactive input
    })
  }

  # Interactive input
  cli::cli_alert_warning("No code provided and clipboard is empty")

  if (interactive()) {
    cli::cli_alert_info("Enter/paste your code (press Enter twice when done):")
    lines <- character()
    repeat {
      line <- readline()
      if (nchar(line) == 0 && length(lines) > 0) {
        break
      }
      lines <- c(lines, line)
    }

    if (length(lines) > 0) {
      return(paste(lines, collapse = "\n"))
    }
  }

  cli::cli_alert_danger("No code to {action_name}")
  return(NULL)
}
